  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "First, make the hummus. Blend the chickpeas with a clove of garlic and the specified amount of the chickpea water from the tin (aquafaba)."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Add the tahini and blend before adding the ice cubes. Blend again, then add the lemon juice, cumin and salt. Adjust the seasoning and consistency to your taste."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "For the harissa tomatoes, add a good drizzle of olive oil to a pan on medium high heat. Add half of the tomatoes and stir often while they cook for about 5-8 mins. They should have broken down and have turned into a sauce. Then add the rest of the tomatoes with the za'atar and the harissa and cook for a few more minutes until they have just burst open."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Cook the couscous according to package instructions."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Toast your pine nuts in a dry pan for a couple of minutes, shaking often to make sure they don’t burn. Roughly chop some parsley."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "To serve, layer the hummus with the tomatoes and couscous and top with pine nuts, parsley and a good drizzle of olive oil."
    }
  ],
